lysis of the meaning of contract theory and a testing of the inherent validity of the ideas of consent and obligation. He uncovers the critical relationship between the act of willing and that of consenting in self-government and shows how "will" relates to political legitimacy. His is the first large-scale study of social contract theory from Hobbes to Rawls that gives "will" the central place it occupies in contractarian thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGesellschaftsvertrag. 0aKritik. 0aPolitieke filosofie. 0aPolitik. 0aPolitische Philosophie. 0aSociaal contract. 0aSocial contract. 0aSozialvertrag. 0aTeoria geral do estado. 0aTeoria politica. 0aTheorie. 0aTheorieën. 0aTheorieën. 4aPHILOSOPHY / General. 4aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General. 4aSocial contract -- History. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Law & Political Science eBook Packagez9783110353495oZDB-23-HLP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067443549040uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067443550640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674435506423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674435506.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HLP